<h1 class="doc-page-title">COMPASS Features</h1>
<p class="doc-page-lead">COMPASS provides a comprehensive suite of features for strategic delivery, compliance management, and performance monitoring.</p>

                <h2 id="products">Products and services</h2>
                
                <p>COMPASS provides a centralised view of all DfE products and services, with real-time integration to the FIPS CMS system.</p>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Key capabilities:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Product catalogue:</strong> Browse and search all DfE products and services</li>
                    <li><strong>Real-time data:</strong> Product information is fetched directly from FIPS CMS API on demand</li>
                    <li><strong>Product dashboards:</strong> View comprehensive information about each product including RAID items, metrics, and assessments</li>
                    <li><strong>Product linking:</strong> Associate RAID items, metrics, and assessments with specific products</li>
                    <li><strong>Status tracking:</strong> Monitor product lifecycle status and health</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="alert alert-info">
                    <p class="mb-0">Product data is fetched in real-time from the FIPS CMS API, ensuring you always have the most current information. Business areas are cached for 1 hour to improve performance.</p>
                </div>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="raid">Product governance</h2>
                
                <p>The product governance system provides comprehensive tracking and management of Risks, Actions, Issues, and Decisions with advanced classification and filtering capabilities.</p>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Risk management</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Risk register:</strong> Maintain a comprehensive register of identified risks</li>
                    <li><strong>Risk assessment:</strong> Evaluate risks using impact and likelihood scoring (1-5 scale)</li>
                    <li><strong>Multi-select risk types:</strong> Classify risks with multiple types simultaneously (strategic, operational, financial, technical, security, etc.)</li>
                    <li><strong>Risk tiers:</strong> Assign risks to governance tiers (project, programme, portfolio, department, cross-government)</li>
                    <li><strong>Business area classification:</strong> Categorise risks by organisational business area</li>
                    <li><strong>Mitigation tracking:</strong> Document and monitor risk mitigation actions with residual risk assessment</li>
                    <li><strong>Risk ownership:</strong> Assign risk owners with intelligent staff autocomplete</li>
                    <li><strong>Strategic alignment:</strong> Link risks to strategic objectives</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Issue management</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Issue log:</strong> Track all identified issues affecting products or services</li>
                    <li><strong>Issue prioritisation:</strong> Categorise issues by severity (critical, high, medium, low) and priority</li>
                    <li><strong>Business area tracking:</strong> Classify issues by organisational business area</li>
                    <li><strong>Blocked flag:</strong> Mark issues as blocked when progress cannot continue</li>
                    <li><strong>Resolution tracking:</strong> Monitor issue resolution progress and timelines</li>
                    <li><strong>Workaround documentation:</strong> Document temporary workarounds while resolution is in progress</li>
                    <li><strong>Impact assessment:</strong> Document the impact of issues on products and services</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Action management</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Action tracking:</strong> Create and monitor action items</li>
                    <li><strong>Action sources:</strong> Track action origins (risk, issue, milestone, service assessment)</li>
                    <li><strong>Business area classification:</strong> Categorise actions by organisational business area</li>
                    <li><strong>Parent-child actions:</strong> Create sub-actions for complex tasks</li>
                    <li><strong>Action ownership:</strong> Assign action owners with intelligent staff autocomplete</li>
                    <li><strong>Due date monitoring:</strong> Track action due dates and completion status</li>
                    <li><strong>Action linking:</strong> Associate actions with risks, issues, and milestones</li>
                    <li><strong>Evidence tracking:</strong> Link to supporting evidence and documentation</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Milestone tracking</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Milestone management:</strong> Track key project and product milestones</li>
                    <li><strong>Business area classification:</strong> Categorise milestones by organisational business area</li>
                    <li><strong>Milestone linking:</strong> Associate milestones with risks, issues, and actions</li>
                    <li><strong>Progress monitoring:</strong> Track milestone status and completion with progress percentages</li>
                    <li><strong>Timeline tracking:</strong> Monitor baseline vs. actual completion dates</li>
                    <li><strong>Strategic alignment:</strong> Link milestones to strategic objectives</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="card border-primary mt-3">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h4 class="h6">Multi-dimensional classification</h4>
                        <p class="mb-0">RAID items can be classified across multiple dimensions including strategic objective, product, business area, and type-specific attributes. This enables powerful filtering, reporting, and analysis capabilities.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="performance">Operational reports</h2>
                
                <p>COMPASS supports comprehensive performance tracking at both product and enterprise levels.</p>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Product performance metrics</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Metric definitions:</strong> Configure custom performance metrics for each product</li>
                    <li><strong>Data submission:</strong> Product teams submit metric values regularly</li>
                    <li><strong>Historical tracking:</strong> View performance trends over time</li>
                    <li><strong>Target setting:</strong> Define and monitor performance targets</li>
                    <li><strong>Visualisation:</strong> Charts and graphs for easy interpretation</li>
                    <li><strong>Value types:</strong> Support for text, numbers, decimals, and percentages (0-100%)</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Enterprise metrics</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Portfolio-wide metrics:</strong> Track high-level enterprise KPIs</li>
                    <li><strong>Aggregated reporting:</strong> Roll up product-level metrics to enterprise level</li>
                    <li><strong>Strategic alignment:</strong> Link metrics to strategic objectives</li>
                    <li><strong>Executive dashboards:</strong> High-level views for leadership</li>
                    <li><strong>Value types:</strong> Support for text, numbers, decimals, and percentages (0-100%)</li>
                </ul>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="enterprise">Enterprise reporting</h2>
                
                <p>Enterprise reporting features provide strategic oversight across the entire product portfolio.</p>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Key features:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Enterprise metrics dashboard:</strong> View and submit enterprise-level KPIs</li>
                    <li><strong>Functional standards assessments:</strong> Conduct and track DDaT functional standards compliance</li>
                    <li><strong>Portfolio analysis:</strong> Analyse performance across the product portfolio</li>
                    <li><strong>Trend analysis:</strong> Identify patterns and trends across products and metrics</li>
                </ul>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="standards">Functional standards</h2>
                
                <p>COMPASS provides comprehensive support for DDaT functional standards compliance tracking.</p>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Standards framework:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Standards library:</strong> Browse all DDaT functional standards</li>
                    <li><strong>Themes and practice areas:</strong> Navigate standards by theme and practice area</li>
                    <li><strong>Criteria definitions:</strong> View detailed criteria for each standard</li>
                    <li><strong>Assessment workflow:</strong> Conduct structured assessments against standards</li>
                    <li><strong>Evidence capture:</strong> Document evidence of compliance</li>
                    <li><strong>Scoring and grading:</strong> Rate compliance levels for each criterion</li>
                    <li><strong>Historical assessments:</strong> Track compliance progress over time</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="alert alert-success">
                    <p class="mb-0">Functional standards data can be synchronised from the DfE Standards CMS to ensure alignment with the latest standards framework.</p>
                </div>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="reports">Reports and dashboards</h2>
                
                <p>COMPASS provides a range of reports and dashboards for different audiences and purposes.</p>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Available reports:</h3>

                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
                        <div class="card">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <h4 class="h6">Risks and issues report</h4>
                                <p class="small">Comprehensive table-based report showing all active risks and issues with filtering and export capabilities.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
                        <div class="card">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <h4 class="h6">Analysis report</h4>
                                <p class="small">Visual analysis of RAID data including distribution by type, status, and product.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
                        <div class="card">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <h4 class="h6">Product dashboard</h4>
                                <p class="small">Detailed view of a specific product including RAID items, metrics, and assessments.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
                        <div class="card">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <h4 class="h6">Performance trends</h4>
                                <p class="small">Historical performance data visualised as line charts and trend indicators.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Report features:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Filtering:</strong> Filter reports by product, date range, status, owner, and more</li>
                    <li><strong>Sorting:</strong> Sort data by any column for easy analysis</li>
                    <li><strong>Export:</strong> Export reports to Excel, PDF, or CSV</li>
                    <li><strong>Personalisation:</strong> Save report preferences and filters</li>
                    <li><strong>Scheduled delivery:</strong> Schedule automatic report generation and delivery</li>
                </ul>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="administration">Administration</h2>
                
                <p>Administrators have access to additional features for system configuration and management.</p>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">User management:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>User accounts:</strong> Create and manage user accounts</li>
                    <li><strong>Role assignment:</strong> Assign administrator or standard user roles</li>
                    <li><strong>Permission management:</strong> Control access to features and data</li>
                    <li><strong>User preferences:</strong> Configure user-specific settings</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">System settings:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Risk types:</strong> Configure available risk categories</li>
                    <li><strong>Risk tiers:</strong> Define risk tier levels</li>
                    <li><strong>Action sources:</strong> Manage action source types</li>
                    <li><strong>Metric definitions:</strong> Create and configure performance metrics</li>
                    <li><strong>Strategic objectives:</strong> Define and manage organisational objectives</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Data management:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Data quality:</strong> Monitor and maintain data quality</li>
                    <li><strong>Audit logging:</strong> Track changes and user activities</li>
                    <li><strong>Data export:</strong> Export data for backup or analysis</li>
                    <li><strong>Integration monitoring:</strong> Monitor API integrations with external systems</li>
                </ul>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="dashboard">Personalised dashboard</h2>
                
                <p>The COMPASS homepage provides a personalised, filterable dashboard that aggregates all items assigned to or owned by the logged-in user. It serves as your command centre for managing all your work in one place.</p>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Dashboard layout:</h3>
                <p>The dashboard uses a clean, tabbed interface with horizontal navigation:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Tab-based navigation:</strong> Switch between different views using horizontal tabs at the top</li>
                    <li><strong>Badge counts:</strong> Each tab shows the count of items with overdue items highlighted in red</li>
                    <li><strong>Always-visible filters:</strong> Filter controls remain accessible as you switch between tabs</li>
                    <li><strong>Responsive design:</strong> Works seamlessly on desktop, tablet, and mobile devices</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Dashboard views:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Overview:</strong> Summary cards showing counts across all item types with colour-coded status indicators
                        <ul>
                            <li>My products count with clickable card</li>
                            <li>Open/total issues showing proportion</li>
                            <li>Active/total risks showing proportion</li>
                            <li>Urgent/total actions (urgent = due within 7 days)</li>
                            <li>Urgent/total milestones</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Products view:</strong> Products where you are a product contact
                        <ul>
                            <li>Shows FIPS ID, title, phase, and your role</li>
                            <li>Quick action buttons to view risks, issues, actions, and milestones for each product</li>
                            <li>Link to full product reporting area</li>
                            <li>No filters (products list is unfiltered)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Issues view:</strong> All issues you own
                        <ul>
                            <li>Filterable by status, severity, and time period</li>
                            <li>Displays severity, status, and target resolution date</li>
                            <li>Highlights overdue issues in red</li>
                            <li>Shows blocking status</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Risks view:</strong> All risks you own
                        <ul>
                            <li>Filterable by status, risk score range, and time period</li>
                            <li>Shows risk score, impact, likelihood, and status</li>
                            <li>Colour-coded by risk severity (red for critical, amber for high)</li>
                            <li>Highlights overdue risks</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Actions view:</strong> All actions assigned to you
                        <ul>
                            <li>Filterable by status, priority, and time period</li>
                            <li>Displays priority, status, and due date</li>
                            <li>Highlights overdue actions in red</li>
                            <li>Highlights urgent actions (due within 7 days) in amber</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Milestones view:</strong> All milestones you own
                        <ul>
                            <li>Filterable by status and time period</li>
                            <li>Shows status, progress percentage, and due date</li>
                            <li>Visual progress bars for each milestone</li>
                            <li>Highlights overdue and urgent milestones</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Dashboard filters:</h3>
                <p>Each view (except overview and products) has powerful filtering options:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Time period filters:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>All time - no date filtering</li>
                            <li>Overdue - items past their due date</li>
                            <li>Due today - items due within the current day</li>
                            <li>Due this week - items due within the next 7 days</li>
                            <li>Due this month - items due within the next 30 days</li>
                            <li>Due next month - items due between 30-60 days</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Status filters:</strong> Context-sensitive based on item type (open, in progress, complete, etc.)</li>
                    <li><strong>Priority/Severity filters:</strong> Filter by priority level or severity rating</li>
                    <li><strong>Auto-submit:</strong> Filters apply immediately as you change them</li>
                    <li><strong>Clear filters:</strong> One-click reset to view all items</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Visual indicators and features:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Colour-coded badges:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Red badges and rows indicate overdue items requiring immediate attention</li>
                            <li>Amber badges indicate urgent items due within 7 days</li>
                            <li>Status badges show current state (open, in progress, complete, etc.)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Priority items section:</strong> Automatically surfaces the most important items at the top</li>
                    <li><strong>Milestone progress bars:</strong> Visual representation of completion percentage</li>
                    <li><strong>Quick actions:</strong> Direct links to edit items without leaving the dashboard</li>
                    <li><strong>Empty states:</strong> Helpful messages when no items match filters</li>
                    <li><strong>Responsive counts:</strong> Badge counts update based on applied filters</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="alert alert-success">
                    <p class="mb-0"><i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> <strong>Tip:</strong> Make checking your dashboard part of your daily routine. Start each day by reviewing overdue items and planning your priorities using the time period filters.</p>
                </div>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2>Filtering and personalisation</h2>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Advanced filtering capabilities:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Summary cards:</strong> View open, closed, and overdue counts at a glance</li>
                    <li><strong>Dimension filters:</strong> View all items, items assigned to you, or items from your preferred business areas</li>
                    <li><strong>Multi-select filters:</strong> Filter by multiple products simultaneously using enhanced Select2 dropdowns</li>
                    <li><strong>Type-specific filters:</strong> Filter risks by score/impact/likelihood, issues by severity/priority, actions by source</li>
                    <li><strong>Tabbed views:</strong> Separate active and closed item tabs with filtered counts</li>
                    <li><strong>Business area filtering:</strong> Filter by specific business areas from CMS</li>
                    <li><strong>Status filtering:</strong> Filter by current status for each entity type</li>
                    <li><strong>Time-based filtering:</strong> Filter by overdue items or items due in specific timeframes</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">User preferences:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Preferred business areas:</strong> Set your preferred business areas in My Settings</li>
                    <li><strong>Automatic filtering:</strong> Index views auto-filter to your preferred business areas</li>
                    <li><strong>Easy override:</strong> Quickly switch to view all items or different business areas</li>
                    <li><strong>Assigned to me sections:</strong> Dedicated sections showing your owned/assigned items on all index pages</li>
                </ul>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2>Additional features</h2>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Staff integration</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Intelligent autocomplete:</strong> Search for DfE staff members as you type when assigning owners or contacts</li>
                    <li><strong>Azure Entra ID integration:</strong> Automatically populate staff details from the directory</li>
                    <li><strong>Rich staff information:</strong> View name, email, job title, and department in autocomplete results</li>
                    <li><strong>Select2 integration:</strong> Modern, searchable dropdowns with keyboard navigation</li>
                    <li><strong>Graceful fallback:</strong> Works with mock data during development or if API is unavailable</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5">Contextual help</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Info modals:</strong> Click info icons on forms to view detailed field guidance</li>
                    <li><strong>Impact/likelihood guidance:</strong> Understand the 1-5 rating scales with examples</li>
                    <li><strong>Severity/priority help:</strong> Clear definitions with response time expectations</li>
                    <li><strong>Risk response strategies:</strong> Guidance on choosing avoid, mitigate, transfer, or accept strategies</li>
                    <li><strong>Inline help text:</strong> Context-sensitive help throughout the application</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5">Data quality and validation</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Required field validation:</strong> Clear indication of required fields with validation messages</li>
                    <li><strong>Foreign key validation:</strong> Prevents orphaned records and maintains data integrity</li>
                    <li><strong>Soft delete:</strong> Records are marked as deleted rather than removed, preserving history</li>
                    <li><strong>Audit trail:</strong> All entities track creation and modification timestamps</li>
                    <li><strong>Unique constraints:</strong> Prevents duplicate codes and identifiers in lookup tables</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5">Accessibility and usability</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>GOV.UK Design System:</strong> Accessible, user-friendly interface compliant with government standards</li>
                    <li><strong>Dark mode:</strong> Toggle between light and dark themes for comfortable viewing</li>
                    <li><strong>Responsive design:</strong> Works on desktop, tablet, and mobile devices</li>
                    <li><strong>Keyboard navigation:</strong> Full keyboard accessibility support</li>
                    <li><strong>Screen reader support:</strong> ARIA labels and semantic HTML for assistive technologies</li>
                    <li><strong>Colour and icon indicators:</strong> Multiple visual cues (not relying on colour alone)</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5">Database and infrastructure</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Azure SQL Database:</strong> Enterprise-grade database for all environments (development, test, production)</li>
                    <li><strong>Data migration utilities:</strong> Tools for migrating and seeding data between databases</li>
                    <li><strong>Entity Framework Core:</strong> Modern ORM with migration support</li>
                    <li><strong>Connection retry logic:</strong> Automatic retry for transient database connection failures</li>
                    <li><strong>Performance optimization:</strong> Indexed columns and efficient querying strategies</li>
                </ul>

